        HEY_YOU_I_LL_HAVE_YOU_KNOW_THAT                                                    = 3206,  -- Hey, you! I'll have you know that only the rightful leader of the Star Onion Brigade can sit there! Get down right now before I charge you with trees-on and disturbing the peas!
        I_DON_T_KNOW_HOW_YOU_GOT_INSIDE                                                    = 3207,  -- I don't know how you got inside, but that area is off limits. Vacate the premises immediately!
        HE_HE_HERE_S_YOUR_DELIVERY_WHEEZE                                                  = 3208,  -- He...he...here's your delivery...<wheeze>...!
        THANKS_ONCE_AGAIN_LIGHT_ON_YOUR_FEET_TODAY                                         = 3209,  -- Thanks once again. Light on your feet today, I see!
        WALKING_TREES_HOW_POSITIVELY_PECULIAR_ARE_THESE_ALSO                               = 3210,  -- Walking trees!? How positively...peculiar. Are these also creations conjured up with Tarutaru magic?
        I_AM_MELEK_THE_CONSUL_OF_BASTOK                                                    = 3211,  -- I am Melek, the consul of Bastok.
        DO_YOU_KNOW_OF_THE_REPUBLIC_OF_BASTOK                                              = 3212,  -- Do you know of the Republic of Bastok? It is a land far across the seas to the west of Windurst, with a rich mining town as its capital.
        WINDURST_BASTOK_AND_SAN_D_ORIA_FOUGHT_TOGETHER                                     = 3213,  -- Windurst, Bastok and San d'Oria fought together in the Great War of twenty years ago and formed a friendly alliance with Jeuno at its head.
        THAT_IS_WHY_EACH_COUNTRY_HAS_CONSULATES_SET                                        = 3214,  -- That is why each country has consulates set up in each other's capitals.
        WHAT_IS_IT_YOU_WANT                                                                = 3215,  -- ...... What is it you want?
        SORRY_BUT_I_M_NOT_MUCH_OF_A                                                        = 3216,  -- Sorry, but I'm not much of a talker. If you have no business with me, then don't speak to me.
        BASTOK_IS_SURROUNDED_BY_A_MOUNTAIN_RANGE_AND                                       = 3217,  -- Bastok is surrounded by a mountain range and has many Galka living in it, so it seems to have the image of an untamed land.
        BUT_THERE_ARE_ROMANTIC_SPOTS_SUCH_AS_THE                                           = 3218,  -- But there are romantic spots, such as the view of the drawbridge at sunset. If you are out to make sweet memories in Bastok, you can't go wrong in that area.
        HIYA_THIS_IS_THE_CONSULATE_OF_BASTOK_IT                                            = 3219,  -- Hiya! This is the Consulate of Bastok. It's a little piece of Bastok that's like an oasis in the midst of Windurst.
        OH_IT_S_NOT_THAT_I_DISLIKE_WINDURST                                                = 3220,  -- Oh, it's not that I dislike Windurst. The beauty of this place is superb, with not a speck of dirt in sight.
        I_GUESS_THAT_S_BECAUSE_THE_TARUTARU_LINE                                           = 3221,  -- I guess that's because the Tarutaru line of vision is so close to the ground, that they don't let a single thing that's been dropped slip by them.
        BEFAW_THE_GREAT_WAR_THERE_WEREN_T_NAWN                                             = 3222,  -- Befaw the Great War, there weren't nawn of these here consulawtes. So whens yaw went to a fawreign country, yaw felt awl alone.
        I_M_ROOLY_JEALOUS_OF_TRAVELERS_TAWDAY_IF                                           = 3223,  -- I'm rooly jealous of travelers tawday. If anything happens to them, theys can just go to the nearest consulawte faw help.
        OH_YOU_HAVE_SOME_BUSINESS_WITH_CONSUL_MELEK                                        = 3224,  -- Oh, you have some business with Consul Melek? Then please head into her office through that door there.
        I_AM_MELEK_THE_CONSUL_OF_BASTOK_I                                                  = 3225,  -- I am Melek, the consul of Bastok. I trust you had a safe sail here?
        SO_YOU_ARE_THE_ONE_WHO_ACCEPTED_THE                                                = 3226,  -- So, you are %...the one who accepted the cooperative mission to Windurst, I see?
        WELL_THEN_GOLD_SKULL_WHY_DON_T_YOU                                                 = 3227,  -- Well then, Gold Skull, why don't you start by informing our fair citizen here about what the mission involves?
        ALLOW_ME_TO_EXPLAIN                                                                = 3228,  -- Allow me to explain...
        THE_MISSION_FROM_OUR_COMRADES_IN_WINDURST_ENTAILS                                  = 3229,  -- The mission from our comrades in Windurst entails the oblation of magic weapons to Giddeus, the frontline to the abode of the Yagudo beastmen.
        ONE_OF_THE_MAGIC_WEAPONS_TO_BE_DEDICATED                                           = 3230,  -- One of the magic weapons to be dedicated to Giddeus will be handed to you at Heavens Tower, here in Windurst.
        YOUR_ORDERS_ARE_TO_HELP_CARRY_THOSE_MAGICAL                                        = 3231,  -- Your orders are to help carry those magical weapons to the Yagudo treasure chamber, deep beneath Giddeus.
        YOU_LOOK_PERPLEXED_YES_WELL_I_GUESS_IF                                             = 3232,  -- You look perplexed. Yes, well, I guess if you put it frankly, you are carrying a tribute to a pack of beastmen.
        YOU_SEE_IN_ORDER_TO_MAINTAIN_THE_PEACE                                             = 3233,  -- You see...in order to maintain the peace of their country, the Windurstians have formed amicable relations with the Yagudo.
        BUT_AS_YOU_VE_PROBABLY_REALIZED_IT_S                                               = 3234,  -- But, as you've probably realized, it's hard to call their relationship amicable when you witness the outrageous behavior of the Yagudo.
        SO_WE_HAVE_TO_TRY_TO_CURTAIL_THE                                                   = 3235,  -- So we have to try to curtail the beastmen's military potential without losing the trust of Windurst.
        THAT_S_WHERE_YOUR_REAL_PURPOSE_COMES_IN                                            = 3236,  -- That's where your real purpose comes in. Gold Skull, please explain the rest of the mission...
        AFTER_RECEIVING_THE_MAGICAL_WEAPONS_FROM_HEAVENS_TOWER                             = 3237,  -- After receiving the magical weapons from Heavens Tower in the Windurst Walls district, you are to return here to the Consulate of Bastok and present the weapons to us.
        WE_WILL_EXCHANGE_THESE_WITH_A_DIFFERENT_WEAPON                                     = 3238,  -- We will exchange these with a different weapon, which you will take to Giddeus as an offering instead.
        DO_YOU_UNDERSTAND_YOUR_ORDERS_OF_COURSE_THE                                        = 3239,  -- Do you understand your orders? Of course, the fact that we are switching weapons is to remain top secret.
        WE_ARE_FORBIDDEN_FROM_MEDDLING_IN_THE_INTERNAL                                     = 3240,  -- We are forbidden from meddling in the internal affairs of another country. However, we wish to save Windurst from its dangerous predicament.
        WELL_YOU_HAD_BETTER_GET_GOING_I_PRAY                                               = 3241,  -- Well, you had better get going. I pray that your mission is a success.
        ASK_GOLD_SKULL_FOR_FURTHER_EXPLANATION_IF_YOU                                      = 3242,  -- Ask Gold Skull for further explanation if you need clarification. I pray that your mission is a success.
        YOU_ARE_TO_PROCEED_TO_HEAVENS_TOWER_AND                                            = 3243,  -- You are to proceed to Heavens Tower and obtain a shipment of magical weapons. Then you are to return back here to the Consulate of Bastok at once.
        ONCE_WE_HAVE_SWITCHED_THE_WEAPONS_YOU_ARE                                          = 3244,  -- Once we have switched the weapons, you are to head to Giddeus and offer them to the Yagudo. Dismissed!
        YOU_RE_WONDERING_WHAT_YOU_SHOULD_DO_IF                                             = 3245,  -- You're wondering what you should do if the Yagudo realize you switched weapons on them, aren't you?
        WELL_THAT_S_WHERE_YOUR_ABILITIES_AS_AN                                             = 3246,  -- Well, that's where your abilities as an adventurer come into play. You should be able to think of something, shouldn't you?
        THE_REAL_MAGICAL_WEAPONS_WILL_BE_SHIPPED_BACK                                      = 3247,  -- The real magical weapons will be shipped back to Bastok, where our soldiers will make far better use of them than the Yagudo ever would.
        WAIT                                                                               = 3248,  -- Wait.
        TAKE_THIS_SWORD_TO_GIDDEUS_INSTEAD_GOOD_LUCK                                       = 3249,  -- Take this sword to Giddeus instead. Good luck.
        TAKE_THAT_SWORD_TO_GIDDEUS_GOOD_LUCK                                               = 3250,  -- Take that sword to Giddeus. Good luck.
        WELCOME_BACK_YOUR_MISSION_WENT_WITHOUT_INCIDENT_I                                  = 3251,  -- Welcome back. Your mission went without incident, I trust?
        WE_VE_SENT_THE_REAL_MAGIC_WEAPONS_LIKE                                             = 3252,  -- We've sent the real magic weapons like the one you brought us, back to our homeland. They'll come in useful for expelling the Quadav from around Bastok.
        WELL_I_PRESUME_YOU_HAVE_TO_PROCEED_TO                                              = 3253,  -- Well, I presume you have to proceed to the Consulate of Bastok in San d'Oria next.
        IT_IS_ANOTHER_LONG_JOURNEY_TO_REACH_SAN                                            = 3254,  -- It is another long journey to reach San d'Oria. You have to travel from Mhaura to Selbina by boat first, then follow the land route north for quite a way.
        DON_T_OVERDO_YOURSELF_REST_UP_A_LITTLE                                             = 3255,  -- Don't overdo yourself. Rest up a little before you head to your destination, San d'Oria.
        I_HOPE_TO_SEE_YOU_SAFE_AND_WELL                                                    = 3256,  -- I hope to see you safe and well again someday. Take care, %.
        TO_OVERDO_YOURSELF_IS_TO_WORK_BEYOND_YOUR                                          = 3257,  -- To overdo yourself is to work beyond your natural abilities.
        CARRYING_ON_IN_SUCH_A_WAY_WILL_NOT                                                 = 3258,  -- Carrying on in such a way will not enable you to give good results. Sometimes you simply need to be kind to yourself.
        I_CONSTANTLY_PRAY_I_PRAY_FOR_THE_FUTURE                                            = 3259,  -- I constantly pray. I pray for the future of Bastok.
        TODAY_I_LL_ALSO_BE_PRAYING_FOR_YOU                                                 = 3260,  -- Today I'll also be praying for you to have a safe journey.
        THOSE_YAGUDO_DIDN_T_TAKE_THE_WEAPONS_SHIPMENT                                      = 3261,  -- Those Yagudo didn't take the weapons shipment without giving you trouble, did they?
        BUT_YOU_WERE_QUICK_WITTED_AND_SKILLED_ENOUGH                                       = 3262,  -- But you were quick-witted and skilled enough to overcome it. That's the way of the true Bastoker.
        I_WONDER_HOW_LONG_OUR_COUNTRIES_WILL_KEEP                                          = 3263,  -- I wonder how long our countries will keep cheating on each other?
        THIS_WHOLE_YAGUDO_THING_GOT_MESSY_BECAUSE_THE                                      = 3264,  -- This whole Yagudo thing got messy because the Windurstians tried to play nice with them...
        BOTH_OUR_COUNTRY_AND_JEUNO_SHOULD_TELL_THEM                                        = 3265,  -- Both our country and Jeuno should tell them straight that this isn't going to get them anywhere.
        THE_WINDURSTIANS_ARE_JUST_BEING_USED_BY_THE                                        = 3266,  -- The Windurstians are just being used by the Yagudo.
        I_AM_MELEK_THE_CONSUL_OF_BASTOK_I_2                                                = 3267,  -- I am Melek, the consul of Bastok. I trust you had a safe sail here?
        SO_YOU_ARE_I_HEARD_ABOUT_YOUR_ACTIVITIES                                           = 3268,  -- So, you are %...? I heard about your activities in San d'Oria and am expecting great things from you here too.
        WELL_THEN_WE_SHOULD_GET_STRAIGHT_TO_THE                                            = 3269,  -- Well then, we should get straight to the matter at hand. Gold Skull, why don't you start by informing our fair citizen here about what the mission involves?
        ALLOW_ME_TO_EXPLAIN_2                                                              = 3270,  -- Allow me to explain...
        THE_MISSION_FROM_OUR_COMRADES_IN_WINDURST_ENTAILS_2                                = 3271,  -- The mission from our comrades in Windurst entails the extermination of a giant monster that appeared in the depths of Giddeus, the borderland to the theocracy of the Yagudo beastmen.
        YOU_ARE_TO_RECEIVE_A_KEY_FROM_HEAVENS                                              = 3272,  -- You are to receive a key from Heavens Tower in the Windurst Walls district, and head to the innermost part of Giddeus.
        YOUR_ORDERS_ARE_TO_THEN_DEFEAT_THE_HEINOUS                                         = 3273,  -- Your orders are to then defeat the heinous beast that lurks there.
        YOU_LOOK_PERPLEXED_YES_WELL_I_GUESS_IF_2                                           = 3274,  -- You look perplexed. Yes, well, I guess if you put it frankly, you are protecting a pack of Yagudo beastmen from a ferocious monster.
        YOU_SEE_IN_ORDER_TO_MAINTAIN_THE_PEACE_2                                           = 3275,  -- You see...in order to maintain the peace of their country, the Windurstians have formed amicable relations with the Yagudo.
        BUT_AS_YOU_VE_PROBABLY_REALIZED_IT_S_2                                             = 3276,  -- But, as you've probably realized, it's hard to call their relationship amicable when you witness the outrageous behavior of the Yagudo.
        BUT_IN_ORDER_TO_MAINTAIN_THE_TRUST_OF                                              = 3277,  -- But, in order to maintain the trust of Windurst, we have to participate in this preposterousness.
        WELL_GOOD_LUCK_WITH_YOUR_MISSION_I_LOOK                                            = 3278,  -- Well, good luck with your mission. I look forward to hearing of your success.
        YOU_ARE_TO_RECEIVE_A_KEY_FROM_HEAVENS_2                                            = 3279,  -- You are to receive a key from Heavens Tower, here in Windurst, and to defeat the great monster that has appeared in the depths of Giddeus. That's all your country requires from you.
        JUST_BECAUSE_THE_WINDURSTIANS_ARE_TRYING_TO_BE                                     = 3280,  -- Just because the Windurstians are trying to be friends with the Yagudo doesn't mean we should hold back from continuing our fight with the beastmen.
        GO_AHEAD_AND_SAVAGE_THE_BRUTES_I_SAY                                               = 3281,  -- Go ahead and savage the brutes, I say! If Windurst puts forward an official complaint, I'll handle it for you.
        ASK_GOLD_SKULL_FOR_FURTHER_EXPLANATION_IF_YOU_2                                    = 3282,  -- Ask Gold Skull for further explanation if you need clarification. I pray that your mission is a success.
        YOU_WONDER_WHETHER_SOMETHING_CAN_BE_DONE_ABOUT                                     = 3283,  -- You wonder whether something can be done about the amicable relationships between Windurst and the Yagudo? I think it's a hopeless cause, personally.
        THE_TARUTARU_ARE_LIKE_PUPPETS_HAVING_THEIR_STRINGS                                 = 3284,  -- The Tarutaru are like puppets having their strings pulled in the name of peace. But then again, it is nice to have peace, even if it is only skin-deep.
