        I_SHAN_T_CAUSE_THEE_TEEN_ALL_I                                                     = 16064,  -- I shan't cause thee teen. All I ask is that thou wearest this % upon thy finger and let thyself bathe in its luminescent emanations.
        WEAREST_THAT_UPON_THY_FINGER_AND_LET_THYSELF                                       = 16065,  -- Wearest that % upon thy finger and let thyself bathe in its luminescent emanations.
        QUOTHA_THE_LIGHT_THAT_SHINES_FORTH_FROM_THY                                        = 16066,  -- Quotha...the light that shines forth from thy soul hath brightened a considerable degree.
        NATHELESS_IT_REMAINETH_BUT_A_DULL_GLOW_AKIN                                        = 16067,  -- Natheless, it remaineth but a dull glow akin to twitherym dust whenas compared to the blindingly refulgent souls of more accomplished combatants.
        TO_FULFIL_THY_TRUE_POTENTIAL_THOU_NEEDS_ASSUME                                     = 16068,  -- To fulfil thy true potential, thou needs assume the role of gladiator and bathe in monipulator blood.
        AS_A_MONIPULATOR_THOU_HAST_LIKELY_REDUCED_OPPONENTS                                = 16069,  -- As a monipulator, thou hast likely reduced opponents everywhere to bawling babes at the mere mention of thy name.
        SIMULTANEOUSLY_THOUGH_COMBATANTS_WHO_HATH_CUT_SWATHS_THROUGH                       = 16070,  -- Simultaneously, though, combatants who hath cut swaths through adversaries while inside bestial vessels betimes yearneth for more...to bite the hand that feedeth.
        A_SAGA_SUNG_OF_THOSE_WHO_INSTILL_TERROR                                            = 16071,  -- A saga sung of those who instill terror and those who release the land from it... Bwahaha, a worthy tale of spiritual strife, forsooth.
        NOW_THAT_THE_STAGE_HATH_BEEN_SET_I                                                 = 16072,  -- Now that the stage hath been set, I shall impart the extent of my gladiatorial knowledge to thee. Simply ask and thou shalt receive.
        WHAT_SHALL_YOU_ASK_ABOUT_BELLIGERENCY_RANKS_PRESTIGE                               = 16073,  -- What shall you ask about? Belligerency. Ranks. Prestige. Spoils. Domination. Nothing.
        THOSE_WHO_HAVE_THE_AMBITION_TO_SLAY_MONIPULATORS                                   = 16074,  -- Those who have the ambition to slay monipulators can do battle against them by speaking with [me/my Northern San d'Orian ally] or one of my brethren in either [Port Bastok or Port Windurst/Northern San d'Oria or Port Windurst/Northern San d'Oria or Port Bastok] and receiving %.
        THIS_IS_THY_METAPHORICAL_MUSTER_AS_WELL_AS                                         = 16075,  -- This % is thy metaphorical muster as well as official avowal to enter belligerency.
        WHILE_IT_DOTH_PROVIDE_MYRIAD_BOONS_TO_THEE                                         = 16076,  -- While it doth provide myriad boons to thee, it preventeth not those outside thy coterie from interfering with thy duty. Such a benediction will only descend upon the yare souls who hath claimed monipulators as their prey.
        I_MUST_ALSO_CAUTION_THEE_TO_BEWARE_THAT                                            = 16077,  -- I must also caution thee to beware that, depending on thy level of expertise, it may not behoove thee to tread upon the soils of certain lands.
        LASTLY_SHOULD_THY_BLOODLUST_CEASE_OR_RESOLVE_WITHER                                = 16078,  -- Lastly, should thy bloodlust cease or resolve wither on the vine, speak to me and I shall grant thee permission to withdraw from belligerency.
        LASTLY_SHOULD_THY_BLOODLUST_CEASE_OR_RESOLVE_WITHER_2                              = 16079,  -- Lastly, should thy bloodlust cease or resolve wither on the vine, speak to one of my compatriots and they shall grant thee permission to withdraw from belligerency.
        THREE_RANKS_DOTH_SERVE_TO_CLASSIFY_THE_WORLD                                       = 16080,  -- Three ranks doth serve to classify the world's monipulator executioners. There is the eponymous gladiator (Gla), champion gladiator (CG), and high champion gladiator (HCG).
        NAUGHT_ELSE_NEEDS_BE_EXPLAINED_ANENT_THIS_SIMPLE                                   = 16081,  -- Naught else needs be explained anent this simple concept...save that a gladiator's rank is determined by his prestige.
        PRESTIGE_IS_THE_GLADIATOR_S_EQUIVALENT_OF_THE                                      = 16082,  -- Prestige is the gladiator's equivalent of the common adventurer's fame.
        DEFEATING_BOTH_MONSTERS_AND_MONIPULATORS_INCREASETH_THY_PRESTIGE                   = 16083,  -- Defeating both monsters and monipulators increaseth thy prestige, while falling victim to their claws decreaseth it.
        EACH_RANK_ALSO_HATH_A_CORRESPONDING_MAXIMUM_AMOUNT                                 = 16084,  -- Each rank also hath a corresponding maximum amount of prestige, much like the infamy of monipulators.
        ASCERTAINING_THY_CURRENT_PRESTIGE_IS_MERELY_A_TRIFLE                               = 16085,  -- Ascertaining thy current prestige is merely a trifle. (Access the Profile menu under Status.)
        OF_COURSE_PRESTIGE_IS_NOT_SIMPLY_A_MEANS                                           = 16086,  -- Of course, prestige is not simply a means by which to boast to thy inferiors. Thou canst cede it to me in exchange for troves of splendid rewards.
